{
  "doc_id": "23799",
  "text": "The progress of systems for targeted drug delivery has been reviewed by Moghimi et al. [CITATION_1] Previous study on in vitro evaluation of the characteristics of nanoparticles found that some of the most important factors determining nanoparticle cytotoxicity were particle size, particle morphology, surface area, and particle reactivity in solution. [CITATION_2] Researchers have synthesized magnetite particles coated with dextran to enhance the capture of magnetite nanoparticles in capillary tissue. [CITATION_3] Carriers were prepared from poorly soluble drugs by grafting hydrophobic moieties, hydrophilic moieties, and glycidol. [CITATION_4] Novel magnetic iron oxide nanoparticles were also coated with PEI-g-PEG for potential biomedical application.",
